<p>
    This Aviation Obstacle Registration (AOR) application is a student project at the University of Agder.
    It is designed for testing and learning purposes only.
</p>

<h3>Information we collect</h3>
<p>
    - Login data (username and password)<br />
    - User role (e.g., Admin, Registerfører, Crew)<br />
    - Obstacle data (name, description, height, location)
</p>

<h3>How we use the information</h3>
<p>
    Data is used only for authentication and to allow users to register or manage obstacle data.
    We do not share data with third parties, and nothing is used for marketing.
</p>

<h3>Data storage</h3>
<p>
    - In Docker: data is stored in MariaDB.<br />
    - In development: data may be stored temporarily in an InMemory database.<br />
    - Session cookies are used for login and are deleted on logout.
</p>

<h3>User rights</h3>
<p>
    Users can request correction or deletion of their login or submitted obstacle data.
</p>

<h3>Contact</h3>
<p>
    For questions, contact the AOR development team at the University of Agder.
</p>